---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import SoftwareApplicationSchema from '../components/schema/SoftwareApplicationSchema.astro';
import FAQPageSchema from '../components/schema/FAQPageSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const featuresFaqs = [
  {
    q: 'Does Pour Picks work with all bourbon bottles?',
    a: 'Pour Picks covers thousands of American whiskeys, bourbon, rye, Tennessee whiskey, wheat whiskey, and single-malt American. The AI label scanner handles most commercially available bottles. If a bottle is missing or the scan doesn\'t match, users can describe the bottle in text for a second pass, search manually, or suggest an addition to the catalog.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is Pour Picks free to use?',
    a: 'Yes. The core app is free: unlimited browsing, the palate quiz, and basic cellar tracking. A Cask Club subscription ($2.99/month) adds unlimited AI scans, full journaling, advanced cellar tools, and collection value tracking. Subscriptions are billed through Apple, payment information never touches Pour Picks servers.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the AI label scanner?',
    a: 'The AI label scanner, called Pour Concierge, uses Claude Vision to read a bottle\'s front label through your iPhone camera. It identifies the distillery, expression, and proof, then matches the result against the catalog, usually in under a second. If the read isn\'t right, you can correct it or search manually.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How does Pour Picks recommend bourbon?',
    a: 'Pour Picks has two recommendation modes. The palate quiz (3 questions basic, 9 questions advanced) matches your flavor preferences to catalog entries. The "Pour Tonight" feature reads your actual cellar and picks a specific bottle to pour tonight based on what you\'ve poured recently, your personal ratings, and the season, it recommends from what you already own, not purchases.',
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Features"
  description="A closer look at Pour Picks: cellar catalog, tasting journal, AI bottle identification, palate-matching quiz, and a browsable American-whiskey catalog."
  path="/features"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <SoftwareApplicationSchema featureList="Bourbon cellar tracker, AI label scanner, taste quiz, personalized recommendations, tasting journal, Pour Tonight feature" />
    <FAQPageSchema faqs={featuresFaqs} />
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Features', url: `${SITE.url}/features` }]} />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/icon.png" />
  </Fragment>

  <header class="dept-masthead">
    <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
    <h1>Inside the app</h1>
    <p class="dept-lede">Six things it does, and the specific way it does each one. Laid out in the order you would actually use them, from your first scanned bottle to what the shelf is worth.</p>
  </header>

  <ol class="ledger">
    <li class="ledger-entry">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">01</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Cellar</span>
        <span class="ledger-spec">Owned &middot; Wishlist &middot; Finished</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>Your cellar, organized</h2>
        <p>Every bottle by distillery, expression, proof, age, and fill level. Flag each one Owned, Wishlist, or Finished, and log your rating the moment you set the glass down. Filter and search to see what is open, what is still sealed, and what is on the chase list.</p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ledger-entry">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">02</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Catalog</span>
        <span class="ledger-spec">Bourbon &middot; Rye &middot; Tennessee &middot; Wheat &middot; Malt</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>The whole American shelf</h2>
        <p>Browse the full American-whiskey catalog. Filter by distillery, age, proof, or price, or widen to world spirits when you want to look past Kentucky. Every entry carries its mash bill, flavor tags, and food and drink pairings, with a path straight back to your cellar.</p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ledger-entry ledger-entry--feature">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">03</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Pour Concierge</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>Scan the label, get the bottle</h2>
        <p class="ledger-stat">Named and matched, usually in under a second.</p>
        <p>Point your camera at the front label. Pour Concierge reads it with Claude Vision, names the distillery, expression, and proof, and matches it to the catalog. If it misses, describe the bottle in words, search by hand, or add it yourself. Every add carries a 4.5-second undo, so nothing lands in your cellar by accident.</p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ledger-entry">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">04</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Palate</span>
        <span class="ledger-spec">3 questions, or 9</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>Find your next pour</h2>
        <p>Answer three quick questions, or nine if you want to go deep. The quiz maps what you already like to bottles you have not tried yet. Stick to Classics leans on the icons; Surprise Me pushes the deep cuts forward.</p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ledger-entry">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">05</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Journal</span>
        <span class="ledger-spec">Nose &middot; Palate &middot; Finish</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>A journal that remembers</h2>
        <p>Log every pour with one overall rating plus separate marks for nose, palate, and finish. Note how you took it (neat, rocks, water, cocktail), the pour size, and whatever you want to say in your own words. Your aggregate rating shows on the bottle so other collectors know whether to chase it.</p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ledger-entry">
      <div class="ledger-index">
        <span class="ledger-no">06</span>
        <span class="ledger-dept">Value</span>
        <span class="ledger-spec">MSRP, or what you paid</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-body">
        <h2>What the shelf is worth</h2>
        <p>Cellar value updates with every bottle. MSRP is the default; override it with what you actually paid. Per-bottle and per-line totals, with steppers for the ones you own more than one of.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <section class="closing">
    <h2 class="section-title">Start your cellar</h2>
    <p class="cta-body">
      Pour Picks is on the App Store now, free to download. Scan your first bottle
      tonight. If something is off, email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a> and a real person reads it.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="cta" href={SITE.appStoreUrl}>Download on iOS</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
